cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper focuses on the analysis of vehicle-to-infrastructure communication in urban microcellular networks using stochastic geometry. This involves the use of wireless networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also uses a pathloss model and derives closed-form solutions, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and mathematical analysis (cs.MA). The analysis of the coverage probability and the deployment of base stations can be considered as control and optimization problems, respectively, which are related to systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the use of millimeter-wave technology for communication is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
